query.result:
1 I already saw knights move camp, 2 and begin a swarm and show their skill, 3 and sometimes depart for their escape;
4 I saw corridors through your land, 5 O Aretines, and I saw whirl shields, 6 trust tournaments and run a joust;
7 when with trumpets, and when with bells, 8 with drums and with signals of flags, 9 and with things of ours and with strange ones;
10 nor ever with such diverse signals 11 did I see knights move nor foot soldiers, 12 nor ship to a sign of land or of star.

